{
  "text": "For US8 and US10, a physical interaction with classical class I MHC products occurs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , but neither show significant ER retention or down-regulation of class I MHC products to the extent seen for US3, US2, and US11. Although both US8 and US10 bind to classical class I MHC products, only the expression of US10 imposes a delay on their egress from the ER, without affecting overall turnover of assembled class I MHC complexes or free class I MHC heavy chains. Based on our experience with the US2 and US11 products, the observation window of these experiments was limited to short periods only, and was thus biased against the possibility of documenting changes that occur with slower kinetics, yet are quantitatively significant. These experiments also failed to take into account the possibility that some of the HCMV US gene products might target nonclassical class I MHC products, by analogy of the effects reported for US2 and HFE, a class I-like molecule involved in the trafficking of the transferrin receptor [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "42606521",
